    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rio de
                                    Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received January 29.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Thompson reports that at an interview in which interference with the coal
                        trade of British subjects was discussed, the representative of Great
                        Britain, whose views are shared by his Belgian, French, Italian, and
                        Portuguese colleagues, declared that all other means would be exhausted
                        before force would be resorted to and intimated that recognition might be
                        recommended by him.</p>
            </div>
